sample.title: Will Elon Musk‚Äôs Trillion Dollar Pay Package Become The New Norm In The U.S.?
sample.description:
Since the late 20th century CEO pay has exploded, widening the divide between the ultra wealthy and working class Americans. Now, Tesla CEO Elon Musk could set a new standard in CEO pay packages, becoming the first trillionaire CEO after his record breaking pay package was approved in November 2025. Tesla is not alone in this, U.S. mega-cap CEOs like Apple's Tim Cook, Google's Sundar Pichai, and Amazon's Andy Jassy are also seeing their net worth skyrocket, as massive pay packages become the standard across S&P 500 companies. So what is behind these huge pay outs, how do these companies afford them, and is there a payoff or is it just luck?

sample.title: Israel will open Gaza crossing once last hostage body returned | BBC News
sample.description:
Israel says it has agreed to reopen the Gaza Strip's key border crossing with Egypt only after an operation to retrieve the body of the last remaining Israeli hostage in the territory is complete.

The Rafah crossing was meant to have reopened during the first stage of the ceasefire between Israel and Hamas, which began in October.

However, the Israeli government has made that conditional on Hamas making every effort to return the body of the last hostage, police officer Master Sgt Ran Gvili.

On Sunday, Israel's military said it had begun a new search for his remains, saying the operation was taking place at a cemetery in Gaza City and that it could last several days.

sample.description:
The Trump administration is facing pressure to launch a full investigation into the second Minneapolis killing by federal agents in two weeks, as one Republican governor says "enough is enough".
 
US President Donald Trump told the Wall Street Journal his administration is "reviewing everything" and also indicates he could eventually withdraw agents from the city - but he's given no time frame.
 
Alex Pretti, a 37-year-old US citizen, was shot dead on Saturday after an incident with federal agents. 
 
The Trump administration says Pretti carried a gun and posed a danger to officers - while no available video shows him holding a gun.
